**Troubleshooting notes:**
1. Interface showed "up/down" (protocol down) — caused by a cabling issue 
   between Router0 and Switch1. Fixed by re-cabling the connection.
2. Ping between PC0 and Router0 failed completely — traced to a VLAN 
   mismatch: the switch port connected to the router was still in the 
   default VLAN instead of VLAN 10 (PC0's VLAN). Fixed by reassigning 
   that port to VLAN 10.

